Time Series Forecasting¶

Introduction¶

Dataset:¶

  • Contains data of sales and profit of a Furniture company.
  • The time period is year 2014 to 2017.
  • Number of observations: 9994
  • Number of variables: 21
  • Variables to focus: Category and Order Date.
  • Link to download dataset: https://community.tableau.com/docs/DOC-1236

Libraries Used:¶

  1. pandas
  2. numpy
  3. matplotlib
  4. seaborn
  5. Prophet

Modules Used:¶

  1. warnings
  2. from pylab import rcParams
  3. from fbprophet import prophet

Approach:¶

  • Fetched raw dataset.
  • Retrieved 'Furniture' and 'Office Supplies' cateogies.
  • Retrieved corresponding sales.
  • Created Sales forecasting model for 'Furniture' and 'Office Supplies' categories.
  • Retrieved profit for the respective categories.
  • Created Profit forecasting model.
  • Validated models using k-fold-cross-validation.

Libraries to be installed before running the notebook:¶

  1. msgpack
    • anaconda: conda install -c anaconda msgpack-python
  1. fbprophet and pystan
    • anaconda: conda install -c conda-forge fbprophet

Time Alias used:¶

  • Link: http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/timeseries.html#offset-aliases

Prophet Documentation:¶

  • Link: https://facebook.github.io/prophet/docs/installation.html
  • Link: https://github.com/facebook/prophet

2. Data preprocessing¶

2.1 Selecting only required variables¶

In [14]:
warnings.simplefilter("ignore")

cols = ['Row ID', 'Order ID', 'Ship Date', 'Ship Mode', 'Customer ID', 'Customer Name', 'Segment', 'Country', 'City', 
        'State', 'Postal Code', 'Region', 'Product ID', 'Category', 'Sub-Category', 'Product Name', 'Quantity', 'Discount', 
        'Profit']
furniture.drop(cols, axis=1, inplace=True)
office.drop(cols, axis=1, inplace=True)

furniture = furniture.sort_values('Order Date')
office = office.sort_values('Order Date')
  • We have selected only 'Order Date' and 'Sales' variables.

3. Model Creation: Sales¶

3.1 Fitting model on furniture¶

In [22]:
from fbprophet import Prophet
warnings.simplefilter("ignore")

furniture_model = Prophet(interval_width=0.95,daily_seasonality=True)
furniture_model.fit(furniture)
Out[22]:
<fbprophet.forecaster.Prophet at 0x21b4e5a1ba8>

3.2 Fitting model on office¶

In [23]:
warnings.simplefilter("ignore")

office_model = Prophet(interval_width=0.95,daily_seasonality=True)
office_model.fit(office)
Out[23]:
<fbprophet.forecaster.Prophet at 0x21b4e5a1d68>

3.3 Forecasting furniture sales for 3 years¶

In [24]:
furniture_forecast = furniture_model.make_future_dataframe(periods=36, freq='MS')
furniture_forecast = furniture_model.predict(furniture_forecast)

3.4 Forecasting office supplies sales for 3 years¶

In [25]:
office_forecast = office_model.make_future_dataframe(periods=36, freq='MS')
office_forecast = office_model.predict(office_forecast)
